  "Research by Kahneman and Tversky found that the psychological pain of losing money is approximately twice as intense as the pleasure of gaining the same amount, creating a 2:1 pain-to-pleasure ratio.": "",
  "Confirmation bias causes an investor who loves a stock to:": "",
  "Sell the stock immediately": "",
  "Short the stock to hedge their position": "",
  "Research the stock objectively from all angles": "",
  "Seek out positive news and dismiss negative data about the stock": "",
