  "Ignoring past costs when making future decisions, as rational investors should": "",
  "Continuing to hold a losing investment because you've already invested so much, even though past costs should not affect future decisions": "",
  "Selling losing investments quickly to cut losses": "",
  "The sunk cost fallacy occurs when investors hold onto a losing position because they 'already invested so much.' Rational decision-making should focus only on future prospects, not past costs that cannot be recovered.": "",
  "FOMO during a bull market leads investors to:": "",
  "Carefully research before investing, even when conditions shift significantly": "",
  "Diversify into safer assets without accounting for additional influences": "",
  "Buy at high valuations because 'everyone else is making money,' often entering near market peaks": "",
  "Stay completely out of the market when considering all relevant buying factors": "",
